news.title: Redevelopment boost in Maharashtra gives Mhada record payoff
news.para: In just five months, from April to August 2021, MHADA collected Rs 1,171.86 crore through this approach. In comparison, in 12 months from April 2020 to March 2021, the agency had collected 261.38 crore.

news.title: Saya Homes to invest Rs 200 crore in new shopping mall in Noida
news.para: "We are coming up with a shopping centre in Noida. We have acquired a plot in Jaypee township," Saya Homes Managing Director Vikas Bhasin said. The project is expected to be completed in the next two years.

news.title: Delhi: 15,000 flats to be on offer in DDA's new scheme next month
news.para: The proposal to launch the housing scheme would be brought before the authority at its meeting, expected to be chaired by LG Anil Baijal this week.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP issues notices to 10 plot owners in DLF-1 for violating NGT norms
news.para: A DTCP team inspected the licensed colony of DLF-1 after receiving repeated complaints from residents about rampant violations of construction norms. During the inspection, the DTCP staff noticed several violations of NGT norms.

news.title: GR soon on non-agricultural land conversion: Maharashtra revenue minister
news.para: Thorat told TOI that the new guidelines would be issued in a couple of weeks. The conversion of land has become an important issue against the backdrop of increasing urban population and expansion of cities and towns.

news.title: Mumbai: Malaika Arora 'amicably' settles row over Rs 14.5 crore flat delay
news.para: The project is the free-sale component in a slum rehabilitation project promoted by Pyramid Developers and Ultra Lifespaces (formerly known as Satra Buildcon).

news.title: Mumbai: Imperial Infra buys Bandra property for Rs 350 crore
news.para: In late October, Imperial Infra, a Boman Irani-led Rustomjee Group firm, concluded the sale agreement with the Bandra Parsi Convalescent Home Trust for the 1-acre plot near Taj Land's End Hotel.

news.title: Mumbai: Altamount Road villa sold for Rs 99 crore
news.para: ​​According to indextap.com, the property situated near the Ambani residence has been bought by Navisha Properties.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to act against 5,000 illegal buildings
news.para: According to BBMP sources, among the 8,486 approved building plans, as many as 5,223 buildings have been found to be built in violation of the sanctioned plans so far. This amounts to 84 per cent of violations and BBMP has served notices to all the owners.

news.title: Will extend benefits of low interest to homebuyers: Noida, Greater Noida realtors to SC
news.para: The real estate companies further said that Noida and Greater Noida authorities have moved the top court after lapse of more than a year, and termed it as an abuse of the process of law.

news.title: Consortium of PSU banks to infuse about Rs 1,000 crore in Amrapali projects: SC told
news.para: Consortium of six PSU banks, which include UCO bank, Bank of India and Bank of Baroda, among others have agreed in-principle to infuse funds to the tune of around Rs 1,000 crore and paperwork is likely to be completed by the month end.

news.title: PM to transfer over Rs 700 crore to 1.47 lakh PMAY-Gramin beneficiaries in Tripura
news.para: The first installment will be transferred at around 1 pm today via video conferencing, informed an official statement issued by the Prime Minister Office.

news.title: Gurugram: Ninex Developers, directors booked for cheating buyer
news.para: The complainant, Reena Sethi, is a resident of Delhi's Dwarka. She booked a flat in a residential project in Sector 76 for Rs 89 lakh in September 2016. The realtor, Ninex Developers, promised to buy the flat back after a certain period.

news.title: Delhi pollution: Construction activities prohibited from November 14 to 17
news.para: The chief minister, after an emergency meeting, told reporters that his government will also present a proposal for lockdown before the Supreme Court.

news.title: China's Tianjin eases residential permit rules as property market slows
news.para: Tianjin, which shares a border with the capital city Beijing, has been hit by a slowdown in its property market. New home prices in September fell for the first time since October last year.
